H0.text: Trophic levels are the feeding positions in a food chain or web.

H1.text: Secondary levels are the feeding positions in a food chain or web.

H2.text: Producer levels are the feeding positions in a food chain or web.

H3.text: Consumer levels are the feeding positions in a food chain or web.

A4.text: The trophic level of an organism is the position it occupies in a food web.

A5.text: A food web starts at trophic level 1 with primary producers such as plants, can move to herbivores at level 2, carnivores at level 3 or higher, and typically finish with apex predators at level 4 or 5.
